headline: Parker-Hannifin (PH): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q3 Earnings?
summary: Since January 2020, the S&P 500 has delivered a total return of 82%. But one standout stock has more than doubled the market - over the past five years, Parker-Hannifin has surged 207% to $635 per share. Its momentum hasn’t stopped as it’s also gained 24.8% in the last six months, beating the S&P by 18.5%.
